					<physDesc rend="visible">
						<p>Paper codex of early 17th century.</p>
						<objectDesc form="codex">
							<supportDesc material="chart">
								<support>Paper codex. </support>
								<extent>187 folios<dimensions type="leaf" unit="mm">
										<height>305</height>
										<width>200</width>
									</dimensions>
									<dimensions type="written" unit="mm">
										<height>235</height>
										<width>145</width>
									</dimensions>
								</extent>
								<foliation>
									<p>187 folios (+2 modern paper flyleaves at the beginning and at the end). </p>
								</foliation>
								<collation>
									<p>Quires of mostly 8 leaves each. </p>
								</collation>
								<condition>
									<p>One leaf missing after folio 130 and 168 respectively. </p>
									<p>Folio 3 is a recent restoration. </p>
									<p>Folios 1-2 and 186-187 are vellum.</p>
									<p>Several pages water-damaged. </p>
									<p>First few leaves damaged, preserved on paper. </p>
								</condition>
							</supportDesc>
							<layoutDesc>
								<layout columns="2" ruledLines="34" writtenLines="34">
									<p>Some marginal notes and additions. </p>
									<p>Hard-point ruling visible. </p>
									<p>Catchwords on every verso, partly preserved. </p>
								</layout>
							</layoutDesc>
						</objectDesc>
						<handDesc hands="2">
							<summary>Yemenite semi-cursive script of early 17th century. </summary>
							<handNote script="Hebrew" scope="sole">
								<p>
									<locus from="1r" to="2v"/>and <locus from="186r" to="187v"/>due to a different hand, written on vellum.</p>
							</handNote>
						</handDesc>
						<additions>
							<p>Folios 1r-2v, 186r-187vand contain Deuteronomy, chapters 13:7-18, 15:13-16:15, 30:20-31:10: Hebrew text with the sublinear punctuation, Targum with the simple superlinear puntuation, and <name type="person" role="author">Sa'adia Gaon</name>'s Arabic version in Hebrew characters. Has masorah magna and parva.</p>
							<p>
								<name type="person" role="owner">Daṿid ben Sa῾id</name>: stamped, folio 109v. </p>
						</additions>
